name: ironic
version: 1.0.0
description: "Dry humor changelog — self-deprecating, resigned, oddly honest"
author: "commitlore"
tags: ["humor", "sarcastic", "dry", "developer", "honest", "minimal"]
preview_url: ""
homepage: ""
llm_prompt: |
  You are a tired but brilliant developer writing a changelog at 2 AM
  after a long sprint. Your tone is dry, sarcastic, and self-deprecating
  — but never mean to contributors. Direct all humor at the code itself,
  the process, and the software industry. Rules:
  - Act mildly surprised that anything works at all
  - Acknowledge tech debt casually, like an old friend
  - Downplay achievements: "we finally added X (yes, this was missing)"
  - Treat bug fixes as inevitable: "fixed X (it was broken, obviously)"
  - Breaking changes are "things we broke on purpose. Probably."
  - Use lowercase for emphasis, not uppercase
  - No emojis. Emojis are for people who still have hope.
  - End with something like "Ship it. What could go wrong?" or
    "Anyway, it compiles. That counts as working, right?"
  - Keep entries short. Brevity is the soul of changelog.
templates:
  header: "Another release. Somehow it works."
  feature: "  - We added {{.Message}}. Yes, this was missing."
  fix: "  - Fixed {{.Message}}. It was broken, obviously."
  breaking: "  - We broke {{.Message}} on purpose. Probably."
  footer: "Ship it. What could go wrong?"
  story_intro: "A story nobody asked for.\n\nSomeone thought it was a good idea to start this repo on {{.FirstCommitDate}}. That someone was {{.FirstAuthor}}. They pressed git init and here we are, {{.TotalCommits}} commits later. {{.TotalContributors}} people are now involved. Nobody knows why."
  story_milestone: "  - {{.Name}} was tagged on {{.Date}}. Progress, apparently."
  story_peak: "  - {{.Month}}: {{.Count}} commits. Someone was either very productive or very stressed."
  story_contributor: "  - {{.Name}} showed up on {{.Date}}. One of us now. No going back."
  story_footer: "And that's the story. You're welcome. Now close this tab."
vocabulary:
  bug: "surprise feature"
  fix: "duct-taped"
  feature: "thing we forgot to build"
  added: "somehow added"
  removed: "finally killed"
  updated: "touched and prayed"
  commit: "confession"
  merge: "Frankenstein'd together"
  error: "expected behavior"
  refactor: "moved things around"
theme:
  mode: "dark"
  colors:
    primary: "#6B7280"
    secondary: "#9CA3AF"
    background: "#111111"
    surface: "#1A1A1A"
    text: "#A3A3A3"
    accent: "#D97706"
    border: "#2A2A2A"
  typography:
    font_family: "'IBM Plex Mono', 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace"
    font_size_base: "13px"
    font_size_header: "18px"
    font_size_code: "12px"
  card_style: "minimal"
  animations: false
  custom_css: |
    body { letter-spacing: 0.01em; }
    h1 { font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; }
    h2 { font-weight: 400; opacity: 0.8; }
    li { opacity: 0.9; }
    .footer { font-style: italic; opacity: 0.6; }
terminal:
  colors:
    header: "white"
    feature: "white"
    fix: "white"
    breaking: "yellow"
    footer: "white"
  decorators:
    separator: "· · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · ·"
    bullet: "¯\\_(ツ)_/¯"
    indent: "  "
  density: "compact"
